      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical code verification demonstrates expected order of accuracy for governing equations relevant to hemolysis prediction in rotating machinery.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to confirm second-order spatial accuracy of incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Observed order of accuracy 1.94 consistent with theoretical expectation. Power-law hemolysis model implementation verified against analytical solutions for simple shear flows."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Discretization error estimated via systematic mesh refinement study with GCI below 5% for primary quantities of interest.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on FDA centrifugal pump geometry. GCI for area-averaged wall shear stress and hemolysis index below 2% at all five operating points. Final mesh of 4.2 million polyhedral cells selected for production runs. Temporal discretization verified with time-step independence study for unsteady rotating frame simulations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation are documented and sufficiently representative of CPB operating conditions to support MRL 2 assessment.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental dataset documents flow rates (2.5–6 L/min), rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM), and fluid properties (glycerol-water blood analogue at 37°C). Test conditions span the CPB operating envelope. Uncertainty in experimental hemolysis index measurements quantified at ±12% (95% CI) based on repeat testing protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index agrees with experimental measurements within combined numerical and experimental uncertainty bounds at all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements at 5 operating points. Mean absolute relative error 8.3%; all predictions within experimental uncertainty bounds. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion confirmed. Bland-Altman analysis shows no systematic bias across operating range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest computed by the model are directly relevant to the hemolysis decision criterion and clinical endpoint for CPB device evaluation.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the primary regulatory quantities for CPB device hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. CFD model directly computes these quantities via power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. QoI relevance to worst-case operating condition identification confirmed by parametric operating point sweep."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities are conducted on geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties sufficiently similar to the COU to support credibility claims at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry class as the CPB device under assessment. Operating conditions in validation dataset overlap with COU operating envelope. Blood analogue fluid validated against bovine blood hemolysis correlation. Geometric similarity index >0.85 between validation and COU pump configurations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Numerical solver error assessment not required at MRL 2 for this factor; commercial solver documentation provides sufficient basis.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal numerical solver error quantification beyond code verification is not required. Commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent) convergence criteria of 1e-5 for all residuals applied consistently. Iterative convergence monitored via hemolysis index stabilization. No assessment beyond standard convergence monitoring required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2; standard operating procedures and peer review provide adequate control.",
      "rationale": "CFD analyses conducted under documented standard operating procedures with independent peer review of simulation setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing. Two-analyst review process applied to all production simulations. Formal use error quantification not required at MRL 2 for Class II device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assessment not required at MRL 2; selection of turbulence and hemolysis models is justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on established literature precedent for blood pump CFD (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied consistently with FDA benchmark study protocol. Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2 for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model input parameters are identified, sourced from traceable references, and their nominal values are justified for the CPB operating context.",
      "rationale": "Blood density (1056 kg/m3), dynamic viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s at 37°C), and power-law hemolysis constants (C=3.62e-7, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) sourced from peer-reviewed literature with traceability. Pump geometry digitized from FDA benchmark CAD files with dimensional verification. Inlet boundary conditions derived from clinical CPB flow specifications. Input parameter documentation complete and traceable."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
